narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Very good class that teaches you a lot about biomedical microtechnology. Not too much work as long as one goes to lecture and a great professor. One only really needs a intro bio class to benefit from this class. I would recommend it!

Exactly what the course title says. Good class if you're interested in kind of an overview of various micro- and nanotechnologies being developed with an emphasis on their applications to biomedicine. Prof. Fan is very nice and enthusiastic about his subject. No homework, just a midterm, final project and two lab sessions so not a huge time commitment.
